# =========================================================================
# PURE DLA on Orin (no GPU fallback). This build (TensorRT 8.6.13) has:
#   --useDLA  --inputIOFormats  --outputIOFormats  --half2  --int8  --calib
# It does NOT have: --useSafeDLA, --dlaLayerConfig, --allowGPUFallback.
# "Reformat CopyNode for Input Tensor 0" = FP32->FP16/chw->chw16 I/O conversion
# at the network boundary (NOT a model layer; Conv_0..Conv_71 already on DLA).
# Fix = make the I/O match DLA's native format so no reformat is inserted.
# =========================================================================

# Valid fmt tokens accepted by THIS DriveWorks build: chw, chw16, chw32, hwc8 ...
# NOTE: this build's parser REJECTS "dla_linear" (DW_INVALID_ARGUMENT: Invalid TensorFormat).
#       Use chw16 instead -> it produces the same DLA-native FP16 packed I/O (Half[1,C:16,H,W]).

# >>> CONFIRMED WORKING: 100% DLA, "No layer is running on GPU".
# Engine I/O ends up Half[1,3:16,512,1024] -> Half[1,2:16,512,1024] (FP16 chw16-packed).
# Runtime app must feed FP16 chw16 input (use dwDataConditioner) and read FP16 output.
# WATCH the path: it's DLALaneNet/dla_lanenet_latest.onnx (slash between dir and file!).
cd /home/benchdev2/DLALaneNet
/usr/local/driveworks/tools/dnn/tensorRT_optimization \
  --modelType=onnx \
  --onnxFile=/home/benchdev2/DLALaneNet/dla_lanenet_latest.onnx \
  --out=/home/benchdev2/DLALaneNet/dla_lanenet.dla.bin \
  --useDLA=1 \
  --inputIOFormats=fp16:chw16 \
  --outputIOFormats=fp16:chw16 \
  --verbose=1 2>&1 | tee /home/benchdev2/DLALaneNet/dla_io.log
# Note: "Skipping validation due to non-chw input TensorFormat(s)" is informational, NOT an error.

# Fallbacks if chw16 is ever rejected:
#   plain linear (TRT picks DLA packing): --inputIOFormats=fp16:chw --outputIOFormats=fp16:chw

# =========================================================================
# RUNTIME LOAD on Orin — TWO DIFFERENT ARTIFACTS (do NOT confuse them):
#
#   tensorRT_optimization --useDLA=1  => a TensorRT ENGINE (DLA ForeignNode inside).
#     Load via DriveWorks DNN TensorRT runtime. DO NOT pass --cudla=1.
#       ./dla_lanenet --image=1.png --tensorRT_model=dla_lanenet.bin --cudla=0
#     (renaming .bin -> .dla.bin does NOTHING; bytes are still a TRT engine)
#
#   cuDLA standalone (--cudla=1) needs a DLA STANDALONE LOADABLE (kDLA_STANDALONE).
#     Error "cudlaModuleLoadFromMemory ... failed. 7" = you fed it a TRT engine.
#     The DriveWorks tensorRT_optimization tool CANNOT build this (no --safe flag).
#     Build it with trtexec --safe instead:
#       which trtexec; ls /usr/src/tensorrt/bin/trtexec
#       ls /lib/aarch64-linux-gnu/libnvinfer_safe.so*   # safe runtime must exist
#       trtexec --onnx=/home/benchdev2/DLALaneNet/dla_lanenet_latest.onnx \
#         --saveEngine=/home/benchdev2/DLALaneNet/dla_lanenet.dla \
#         --useDLACore=0 --fp16 \
#         --inputIOFormats=fp16:chw16 --outputIOFormats=fp16:chw16 \
#         --buildOnly --safe --verbose
#     Then: ./dla_lanenet --image=1.png --tensorRT_model=dla_lanenet.dla --cudla=1
#     If "Safety is not supported because safety runtime library is unavailable":
#       safe runtime libs (libnvinfer_safe.so) are missing on this install.
# =========================================================================

